1.3 "Modify" or "Modification" means to alter, adapt, translate, combine,
or otherwise create a version requiring copyright permission.

1.4 "Modified Version" means the whole work resulting from a Modification.

1.5 "Derivative Work" means a copyright derivative based on the Program or
any substantial part of it.

1.6 "Distribute" (or "Convey") means making the Program or a Modified Version
available to a third party by any means, including copies, downloads,
repository access, or transmission.

1.7 "Object Code" means any non-source, machine-executable or machine-
processable form.

1.8 "Corresponding Source" means the source code and other materials
reasonably necessary to build, install, run, and modify the Object Code,
including build scripts, interface definitions, and configuration files,
but excluding generally available system components.

1.9 "Remote Network Interaction" means a user's interaction with Program
functionality over a computer network.

1.10 "Covered Work" means the Program, any Modified Version, and any
Derivative Work licensed under this License.

