If distributing Object Code, you must also provide the Corresponding Source
by one of the following methods:

(i) together with the Object Code;
(ii) from the same location at no charge; or
(iii) via a written/electronic offer valid for at least three (3) years.

5. Remote Network Interaction Source Offer

If you operate a Modified Version and users interact with it remotely through
a computer network, you must prominently offer those users an opportunity to
receive the Corresponding Source of your Modified Version at no charge
(excluding ordinary network access costs), through a standard or customary
means of software copying.

For web-based services, a visible link or menu item such as "Source Code",
"Source", or "License & Source" is recommended.

This section does not apply to purely internal use where no third party
remotely interacts with the Modified Version.

6. Scope of Corresponding Source

Corresponding Source ordinarily includes:

(a) modified source files;
(b) build, packaging, and deployment scripts;
(c) interface definitions and configuration files; and
(d) installation information, where reasonably necessary to install and run
    modified versions in a controlled device or environment.

Corresponding Source need not include:

(i) general-purpose operating system components;
(ii) unmodified, generally available tools; or
(iii) independent works that are not part of the Covered Work.

